# Obsidian notes structure (DSA/Notes)

When creating or extending algorithm/pattern notes in this repo, mirror the **Binary Search** / **Line Sweep** layout.

## Folder per pattern

```
Notes/
  {Pattern}/                          # e.g. BinarySearch, LineSweep
    {Pattern} general theory.md         # hub: diagram + template code
    {#}. {Problem Title}.md             # thin problem note → links to general theory
  Excalidraw/
    {Pattern-Name}.excalidraw           # raw drawing JSON + generator scripts
  ExcalidrawEmbeds/
    {Pattern}/                          # topic subfolder (matches Notes/{Pattern})
      Ex-{Pattern_Snake}.md             # Obsidian Excalidraw embed (.md, compressed-json)
```

## 1. `{Pattern} general theory.md` (hub)

- YAML-style tags on line 1: `#patternTag #tle #template` (match existing tags in sibling notes)
- Embed the Excalidraw companion (width 1000):

  `![[ExcalidrawEmbeds/{Pattern}/Ex-{Pattern_Snake} | 1000]]`

- Section `# Complete Code` with a single template solution:

  ` ```python title:{fileName}.py ` … user's naming (`years`, `current`, `best`, etc.)

- **Do not** embed `Excalidraw/*.excalidraw` directly here — use `Ex-*.md` only.

## 2. `ExcalidrawEmbeds/{Pattern}/Ex-{Pattern_Snake}.md` (Obsidian Excalidraw)

- Frontmatter:

  ```yaml
  ---
  excalidraw-plugin: parsed
  tags: [excalidraw]
  ---
  ```

- Standard warning block (switch to EXCALIDRAW VIEW / decompress)
- `# Excalidraw Data` → `## Text Elements` (one line per label + ` ^elementId`)
- `%%` → `## Drawing` → ` ```compressed-json ` (LZString base64 of `.excalidraw` JSON) → closing ` ``` ` → `%%`

Regenerate from `Excalidraw/*.excalidraw` into `ExcalidrawEmbeds/{Pattern}/` when the drawing is edited outside Obsidian.

## 3. `{#}. {Problem Title}.md` (per problem)

- Tags: `#patternTag #Difficulty`
- Short pointer only — **no** duplicate diagram embed, no long code:

  ```markdown
  This problem is a direct application of the {pattern} pattern.
  Checkout the [[{Pattern} general theory]] for more details
  ```

- Wiki link name must match the general theory filename (e.g. `[[Line Sweep general theory]]`).

## 4. Excalidraw visuals

- Prefer **visual** Excalidraw over long prose; minimal text on canvas
- Generous spacing; avoid overlapping elements
- Dotted lines + transparent fills for guide/zone overlays; draw data **on top**
- Use a clear overlapping example when teaching interval/sweep concepts

## 5. LeetCode code (optional)

- Mirror solutions under `LeetCode/Algorithms/{Pattern}/` with problem link in docstring (existing repo convention).

## Reference implementations

- `Notes/BinarySearch/Binary Search general theory.md` → `ExcalidrawEmbeds/BinarySearch/Ex-Binary_Search.md` + `153. …`
- `Notes/LineSweep/Line Sweep general theory.md` → `ExcalidrawEmbeds/LineSweep/Ex-Line_Sweep_general_theory.md` + `1854. …`
- `Notes/LineSweep/1674. …` → `ExcalidrawEmbeds/LineSweep/Ex-1674_Minimum_Moves_to_Make_Array_Complementary.md`
- `Notes/DynamicProgramming/Dynamic Programming general theory.md` → `ExcalidrawEmbeds/DynamicProgramming/Ex-DP_*.md`
